summary: Do you think that villanelle put a blade inside the lipstick and that's why eve gets a cut?
question: Do you think that villanelle put a blade inside the lipstick and that's why eve gets a cut?
answer:
I’ve been thinking about this scene for two days. There are two possibilities in my mind:

1. Villanelle buys the lipstick, uses it first, then sends it with the flower because she knows Eve would wear it like she did with the perfume. And that’s how Villanelle lets Eve know that even though she really likes her, it doesn’t mean that she will let the stab slide without reminding Eve for a bit. Like a little revenge / guilt tripping she wants Eve to feel worse about herself and wants to meet Villanelle more.

2. Plot twists : The flowers and the lipstick are sent by a new female assassin.

I think 1 is more possible if my shitty guess is right, lol.

summary: i don't know if you saw that article about Killing Eve getting a third season before season 2 starts airing. I'm very happy...
question: i don't know if you saw that article about Killing Eve getting a third season before season 2 starts airing. I'm very happy we're getting another season but the article also says that it might be the last one and I don't know how to feel about it. I don't want it to end this soon!
answer: Geez, it took me forever to find the article you’re talking about. I think it’s this one (x)? I wouldn’t take the article too seriously about s3 being the last one because it litterally says “it could be the last”, like the person who writes it just speculates. Also, the article contains some false information, which makes me question the article’s reliability. It’s NOT bbc who owns killing eve, it’s bbc america! So, the whole point of airing s3 first in the UK and then in the US would never happen. Bbc America is owned by bbc studios AND amc, but it’s pretty much an autonomous network/company, so it’s safe to say that bbc doesn’t have a say about killing eve’s fate.

summary: I HAVE A THEORY ABOUT THE DOOR SCENE + THE CLASSROOM SCENE
title: I HAVE A THEORY ABOUT THE DOOR SCENE + THE CLASSROOM SCENE
body:
DOOR SCENE THEORY

so we can see what villanelle is wearing in this scene. that suit (?) jacket with gold embroidered animals on it with the purple turtle neck thing:

she is wearing the same thing in the car chase/ running away scene were she fogs up the window with her breath.

this leads me to believe that this is from the same part of one episode. we can see what eve is wearing also:

if you look closely you will notice that eve had a swat team/ police behind her. which was also seen here:

i believe another part of this episode is

1. eve drinking

2. eve looking out the window with the swat team

i think that eve arranged to meet with villanelle (because it was her job to find her) but then villanelle got away via the window and eve is angry/upset about it (hence the drinking). i have a theory that maybe eve tipped villanelle off so she could get away. here is why:

he says: “this is out of control” to eve

you will notice she is wearing the same thing so it is most likely from the same episode/ plot line. maybe kenny found out that eve saved villanelle. idk let me know what you think and if you can add any more to this theory.

NEXT - CLASSROOM SCENE THEORY

this was one of the promo images released by EW:

(side note: the symbol of the apple has been used throughout their advertising campaign for this season - let me know if you have any thoughts… forbidden fruit reference perhaps?)

so eve is with niko where he works presumably because he is a teacher and they are being intimate and seductive. this corroborates with this image:

then while they are wearing the same outfits, you can see them hitting the emergency button and hastily getting out:

(^sirens are going off in the actual video just btw)

my thought is that maybe villanelle had found them? here is why. you can see villanelle behind eve and eve not noticing (side note: i think its from the same episode because eve is wearing the coat that she is holding in the previous gif and villanelle is dressed like a teacher/ professor):

(side note: the sexual tension i am quaking) 

maybe V is putting something in eves handbag and when she finds it she evacuates? who knows. let me know what you think.
